Meta VideoSeal
https://github.com/facebookresearch/videoseal

How this project uses it:

  * Vendored source: veed_videoseal/assets/attenuation.yaml is copied verbatim
    from VideoSeal's configs/attenuation.yaml. This is the only VideoSeal source
    redistributed in this repository.

  * Runtime dependency: the `videoseal` package itself is NOT redistributed
    here. It is installed separately from PyPI (see scripts/install_videoseal.sh)
    and remains under its own license.

  * Model weights: the VideoSeal checkpoint (y_256b_img.pth) is NOT
    redistributed here. It is downloaded at runtime from dl.fbaipublicfiles.com
    on first use. VideoSeal's README states: "The model is licensed under an MIT
    license." We reproduce that statement for information only; the upstream
    repository is the authoritative source for the terms that apply to the
    weights, and users who need certainty about them should confirm upstream.

